<file path="docs/PLAN.md">
  1: # Gongfu Tea Timer — Design & Implementation Plan
  2: 
  3: ## Context
  4: 
  5: Louie wants a website that is a collection of gongfu-cha (kung fu tea) steep timers. Each tea has a multi-steep schedule; the app tracks which steep you're on, times each steep, alerts on finish, and advances to the next steep (waiting for a tap to start it, matching the real pour-and-drink rhythm). It ships with a rich named-tea preset library plus custom profiles, in a minimal, wholesome, animated UI colored by tea liquor, working on mobile and desktop as an installable PWA.
  6: 
  7: New greenfield project. Location: `/home/louie/Documents/gongfu-tea-timer` (name changeable).
  8: 
  9: ## Decisions (confirmed with user)
 10: 
 11: - **Stack**: Next.js (App Router) + TypeScript + Tailwind + Zustand + Framer Motion + Serwist (PWA)
 12: - **Persistence**: localStorage now, behind a repository interface so a backend (optional login/sync) can bolt on later
 13: - **Alerts on steep end**: sound chime + browser notification + vibration (mobile) + visual — all toggleable in Settings
 14: - **Auto-advance**: steep N ends → alert → app advances to steep N+1 ready → user taps Start when pouring again. Per-profile toggle to disable advancing (stay on steep until manually advanced).
 15: - **Presets**: big named-tea library (~24 teas: Longjing, Bi Luo Chun, Huangshan Maofeng, Anji Bai Cha, Silver Needle, White Peony, Shou Mei, Junshan Yinzhen, Tieguanyin, Gaoshan, Dancong, Da Hong Pao, Rou Gui, Shui Xian, Dong Ding, Jin Jun Mei, Keemun, Dianhong, Lapsang, Sheng Pu-erh (young/aged), Shou Pu-erh, Liu Bao, Chrysanthemum/herbal)
 16: - **PWA**: installable, offline-capable
 17: - **v1 extras (all approved)**: brew log + tasting notes; strength preference (global lighter/stronger scaler) + ±5s mid-steep nudge; tea stash tracker (grams remaining, decrement per session); share custom profile via URL-encoded link
 18: - **Included by default**: dark mode, water temp + leaf/water ratio shown on session screen, profile JSON export/import
 19: 
 20: ## Architecture
 21: 
 22: ```
 23: src/
 24:   app/                    # Next.js App Router
 25:     page.tsx              # Home: tea grid
 26:     session/[teaId]/page.tsx  # Timer session
 27:     profiles/             # custom profile list + editor
 28:     log/page.tsx          # brew log
 29:     stash/page.tsx        # tea stash
 30:     settings/page.tsx
 31:     import/page.tsx       # ?p=<encoded> shared-profile landing
 32:   lib/
 33:     teas.ts               # preset library (typed data)
 34:     types.ts              # TeaProfile, SteepSchedule, BrewSession, StashItem…
 35:     timer.ts              # timestamp-based timer engine
 36:     repo/                 # repository interface + localStorage impl
 37:     audio.ts              # Web Audio chime (unlocked on first Start tap)
 38:     alerts.ts             # notification + vibration helpers
 39:     share.ts              # profile <-> URL codec (base64url JSON)
 40:   store/                  # Zustand stores: session, settings, profiles, log, stash
 41:   components/             # TimerRing, SteepDots, TeaCard, TeaIcon, editors…
 42: ```
 43: 
 44: ### Key technical points
 45: 
 46: - **Timer engine**: timestamp-based (`endsAt = Date.now() + remainingMs`), display via `requestAnimationFrame`; never decrement a counter on interval — survives tab throttling/sleep. Pause stores `remainingMs`. Steep-end detection compares against `Date.now()` on each frame + a backup `setTimeout`.
 47: - **Strength scaler**: multiplier (e.g. 0.8×–1.3×) applied to schedule at session start; ±5s nudge adjusts current steep only.
 48: - **Repository interface**: `ProfileRepo`, `LogRepo`, `StashRepo`, `SettingsRepo` with a `LocalStorageRepo` implementation. Backend later = new impl, zero UI change.
 49: - **Wake Lock API**: keep screen on while a steep runs (feature-detected).
 50: - **Audio autoplay**: `AudioContext` created/resumed inside the Start button handler — always allowed.
 51: - **Notifications**: permission requested only when user flips the toggle in Settings.
 52: - **PWA**: Serwist service worker, manifest with icons, offline precache of app shell + tea data (all local, no external requests at runtime).
 53: 
 54: ## Data model (core)
 55: 
 56: ```ts
 57: type TeaCategory = 'green'|'white'|'yellow'|'oolong-light'|'oolong-dark'|'black'|'puer-sheng'|'puer-shou'|'heicha'|'herbal';
 58: 
 59: interface TeaProfile {
 60:   id: string; name: string; chineseName?: string;
 61:   category: TeaCategory;
 62:   liquorColor: string;        // hex, drives ring/animations
 63:   icon: string;               // key into TeaIcon SVG set
 64:   tempC: number; ratioGramsPer100ml: number;
 65:   steepsSec: number[];        // e.g. [10,15,20,25,35,45,60,90]
 66:   autoAdvance: boolean;       // default true
 67:   custom?: boolean;
 68: }
 69: 
 70: interface BrewSession { id; teaId; startedAt; steepsCompleted; rating?; note?; gramsUsed?; }
 71: interface StashItem   { teaId|customId; gramsRemaining; gramsPerSession; }
 72: ```
 73: 
 74: ## UI / design direction
 75: 
 76: Minimal, warm, wholesome. Soft cream/charcoal backgrounds (light + dark), generous whitespace, rounded cards, one accent = the selected tea's liquor color. Big central circular timer ring that drains and "fills with tea" (gradient of liquorColor). Steep position shown as a row of dots (done / current / upcoming). Custom inline SVG icons per category (leaf, bud, gaiwan, rolled pearl, pressed cake, flower). Framer Motion page/card transitions; gentle glow pulse on steep completion. Use the `frontend-design` skill during implementation for the visual pass.
 77: 
 78: ## Implementation steps
 79: 
 80: 1. **Scaffold**: `create-next-app` (TS, Tailwind, App Router) in `gongfu-tea-timer/`; add zustand, framer-motion, serwist. `git init`.
 81: 2. **Types + tea library**: `types.ts`, `teas.ts` with ~24 curated presets (schedules per category norms, liquor colors, icons).
 82: 3. **Repo layer + stores**: localStorage repos, Zustand stores, hydration-safe (Next SSR ⇒ read localStorage only client-side).
 83: 4. **Timer engine + session screen**: TimerRing, SteepDots, start/pause/skip/±5s, auto-advance flow, wake lock.
 84: 5. **Alerts**: chime (Web Audio, small synthesized gong — no asset needed), notification, vibration, settings toggles.
 85: 6. **Home grid + tea cards + icons**: category-grouped grid, search/filter.
 86: 7. **Custom profiles**: editor (name, category, color, temp, ratio, steep list editor), export/import JSON, share-link codec + import page.
 87: 8. **Brew log**: auto-record session on finish/abandon, rating + note editor, list view.
 88: 9. **Stash**: stash list, grams decrement on session start (uses profile ratio), low-stash hint.
 89: 10. **Settings + strength slider**, dark mode (system + manual toggle).
 90: 11. **PWA**: manifest, icons, Serwist config, offline test.
 91: 12. **Visual polish pass** with `frontend-design` skill; responsive check mobile + desktop.
 92: 
 93: ## Verification
 94: 
 95: - `npm run build` clean; `npm run dev` and drive with Playwright MCP: pick tea → start steep → let finish → verify auto-advance waits for tap; test pause, ±5s, skip.
 96: - Verify timer accuracy after backgrounding tab (timestamp math).
 97: - Test chime fires after user-gesture unlock; notification permission flow; settings toggles persist.
 98: - Create custom profile → export → share link → open import page → profile imported.
 99: - Brew log entry created with rating/note; stash grams decrement.
100: - Lighthouse PWA installability check; offline reload works.
101: - Mobile viewport (390px) + desktop layouts via Playwright screenshots.
102: 
103: ## Out of scope (later)
104: 
105: Backend accounts/sync (repo interface ready), i18n, ambient sounds.
